The heads of the orcish bandits Vaath and Guzud adorn the twin stakes flanking the entrance to the soldiers barracks in Beournna's Well. The infamous raiders will trouble the supply lines of the Lords' Alliance no more.~/*Sono partiti e hanno eretto il loro accampamento in cima all'altopiano. Sembra che abbiano concluso di avere diritto a reclamare la terra attorno al Pozzo di Beorunna. Quest'uomo è un capitano nell'esercito dell'Alleanza dei Lord.*/
@105374 = ~Bruns' Shell~/*Lancia Incantesimo*/
@105375 = ~Bruns Trubenk was a follower of Tyr, who fought bravely in the service of his god in both the ice of the North and the sands of the South. During one of these campaigns, a group of mages accused him of a terrible crime, and after a hasty trial, he was found guilty and sentenced to imprisonment in a timeless realm in the bowels of the earth. A few months later it was discovered that Bruns was innocent, and that a necromancer was to be held responsible for his guilt. In an act of sincere remorse, Sarshid, the abjurer who carried out the sentence, not only freed Bruns but created for him this shell that would save its owner from a similar fate in the future. In addition to protection from his own school of magic, Sarshid also gave the armor protection from the magic of Death to ensure that when Bruns met the necromancer who was the cause of his misfortune, he would not fall victim to the latter's deadly magic. What happened next to Bruns or the necromancer is unknown, and Sarshid was killed shortly afterward by his own companions, who feared that he would once again create something that would finally undermine their power.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
- Immune to Abjuration spells, Death Magic and Imprisonment

Armor Class: 0
Weight: 50
Requirements: 18 Strength

Not Usable By:
 Bard
 Druid
 Mage
 Thief~/*Chi sono io? Sono un seguace del grande dio Cyric! Sono un servitore dell'imminente Giorno del Sole Oscuro! Sono la sua volontà! Quando arrivò il freddo inverno, Morag usò le Parole per porre il suo popolo in un profondo letargo, imprigionando il calore dei getti di vapore nella magica Pietra Origine, assieme a lei e a tutto il suo popolo. Quando Szass Tam era un mago ancora in vita, si trovò ad affrontare un rivale famoso per le sue capacità come evocatore. Dato che non voleva essere sconfitto dal membro di un'altra scuola di magia, Szass Tam si presentò preparato al duello: lanciò dodici palle di fuoco in rapida sequenza, spiazzando così il suo avversario che era preparato ad affrontare le arti della negromanzia. Quando la collana delle palle di fuoco si esaurì, quindi, Tam iniziò a utilizzare i propri incantesimi, mentre l'avversario aveva già quasi consumato tutta la sua forza magica. Comincerò mostrandoti come selezionare i tuoi incantesimi. Sia i chierici che i druidi usano la stessa procedura per preparare le loro magie divine.*/
@105376 = ~Demarasse's Dagger~/*Pugnale di Xanos*/
@105377 = ~This is the personal weapon of the assassin Demarasse. Given his knowledge of enchanting items, it is likely that he designed it himself and crafted it to his specifications. Its main feature is its extraordinary accuracy, and it can probably pass through bone as easily as through butter if handled properly. But if handled improperly, you run the risk of accidentally cutting off a few fingers.

STATISTICS:

